PsorAnalytics

  • PsorAnalytics is an R package that integrates 15 psoriasis cohorts. It provides fast and convenient methods for exploring and visualizing genes of interest. Now, lets start your analysis!

Jingyuan Ning, ningjingyuan@ibms.pumc.edu.cn

2024-12-13

PsorAnalytics is an R package that integrates 15 psoriasis cohorts. It provides fast and convenient methods for exploring and visualizing genes of interest. Now, lets start your analysis!

To access the help documentation for each function, you can type ? followed by the function name, for example ?psor_boxplot

1. R

install.packages('/Users/drning/Desktop/PsorAnalytics/PsorAnalytics_1.0.0.tar.gz')

res=psor_cor(gene.A='PTTG1',
         gene.B='CLEC7A',
         coh='GSE117239',
         sample.includ= c('healthy', 'psoriasis'),
         color='red',
         method='pearson',
         pt.size=1,
         pt.alpha=0.8)

6. 

deg=psor_limma(coh = 'GSE117239',
               gene.colnumber=7,
               logFC.colnumer=1,
               p.colnumber=4,
               logFC.cutoff=1,
               p.use="adj.P.Val", # "P.Value" 
               P.cutoff=0.05,
               color=c("#A6CEE3",'grey', "#1F78B4"),
               gene.marker=c('S100A12','S100A8','S100A9')
               )

#
deg=deg[["data"]]
genes=filter(deg,Type == 'Up')$gene
enrich.res=psor_enrich(genes,
            species='human')
